HEADWORD: Sultan
<hw>Sul"tan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>sultan</ets>
(cf. Sp. <ets>soldan</ets>, It. <ets>sultano</ets>, <ets>soldano</ets>),
Ar. <ets>sult⟦amac⟧n</ets> sultan, dominion. Cf. <er>Soldan</er>.]</ety>
<def>A ruler, or sovereign, of a Mohammedan state; specifically, the
ruler of the Turks; the Padishah, or Grand Seignior; -- officially so
called.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sultan flower</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
